The White House congratulates Iraq on the passage of a revised election law and expresses support for the Iraqi people and their elected government. The US emphasizes its commitment to the Iraqi constitution and its respect for articles addressing the dispute over Kirkuk and the process for constitutional amendments. Despite challenges, the US is ready to help Iraqis find political solutions and build a united country. Iraq will hold elections in 2013 and 2014, and the US is willing to assist with an accurate census to facilitate these elections. The US also acknowledges the important role of the United Nations in preparing for the upcoming elections and pledges to sustain support for the UN mission in Iraq.